leadership_approach|results_process_vision_people|concentrated|results|process|vision|people|Results first, Process next|You lead by deciding what needs to happen, then turning intent into structure, sequence, and repeatable standards. This pattern is strongest when clear outcomes stay connected to visible progress and structure, sequence, and repeatable standards support the work.|Because this is a concentrated pattern, Results carries the strongest pull. Process, Vision, and People are not absent; they are the range to add when the situation needs stronger structure, longer-range direction, or deeper shared confidence.|Define the outcome, decision, or next step that matters most.|Process turns the approach into structure, sequence, and repeatable standards.|Vision extends the approach by adding longer-range direction and future context.|People helps you add trust, communication, and shared confidence deliberately.|active|leadership_approach::results_process_vision_people::concentrated
